 *     - field      {string}            Field name to filter on.
 *     - label      {string}            Display label.
 *     - type       {string}            "choice" | "reference" | "string" | "date".
 *     For type "reference", also include:
 *     - referenceTable     {string}
 *     - displayField       {string}
 *     - displayFields      {string}    Semicolon-separated fields to display.
 *     - searchFields       {string}    Semicolon-separated fields to search.
 *     - referenceSearchField {string}  Optional preferred field for text operators
 *                                      (e.g. starts with/contains/ends with).
 *     - referenceQualifier {string}
 *     - placeholder        {string}
 *     - pageSize           {string}
 *     - minimumInputLength {string}
 *     - orderBy            {string}
 *     - orderDirection     {string}
 *
 * getIdField()
 *   @return {string} Field name used as the record identifier in the detail view URL.
 *
 * getContextMenuItems(record)
 *   Optional. If defined, the table intercepts right-click on every row.
 *   @param  {Object} record - Row data.
 *   @return {Array<{ label: string, iconClass?: string, iconName?: string, action: Object }>}
 *     Each action is a bag of effects — all properties are optional and combinable:
 *       - clipboard  {string}  Text to write to the clipboard.
 *       - href       {string}  URL to navigate to.
 *       - target     {string}  Window target for href (e.g. "_blank"). Defaults to "_self".
 *       - broadcast  {{ eventName: string, payload?: Object }}  AngularJS event to broadcast.
 *
 * getCellContent(field, record)
 *   @param  {Object} field  - Column definition for the current cell.
 *   @param  {Object} record - Row data returned by getTableData().
 *   @return {Object} Cell content object. Required keys:
 *     - layout {string}  "stack" | "inline"
 *     - blocks {Array<{ value: string, className?: string, href?: string }>}
 *
 * getRowClickAction()
 *   @return {Object} Row click behavior and action.
 *     Supported shape:
